Title: Design and Calibration of a 2D Airjet Device for Human Motor Control Study  
Author: Y. Xu and J.M. Hollerbach 
Address: Salt Lake City, Utah 84103  Salt Lake City, Utah 84121  
Affiliation: 1 Sarcos Research Inc.  Dept. of Computer Science, Univ. of Utah,  
Abstract: We describe the design and calibration of a 2D airjet force perturbation device for identification of human joint mechanical properties based on our successful construction of a 1D airjet device [2]. The key advantage in these devices is that they do not impose any motion constraints on human joint movements. Our design combines two airjet actuators in a plane. We present signal processing methods to eliminate from the force measurement the ringing due to the resonance of the force sensor and the inertia force due to the airjet motion. 
