Reference-contexts: The 1D airjet device consists of a fork shaped airjet actuator (Figure 1) and an I-beam type force sensor <ref> [2] </ref>. The air-jet actuator directs flow based on the Coanda effect. The entire actuator sits on the tip of a force sensor. After considering many design possibilities for the 2D airjet device, we chose the design shown in Figure 2 which meets the above requirements.
