Reference-contexts: The arm is instrumented with a damper (Kinetrol's KD-2aa) and springs. The joint motion is monitored by an Optotrak system (Northern Digital Inc.). The force data acquisition and control are done through the Condor system <ref> [3] </ref>. The sampling rates for Optotrak and Condor systems are 500 and 1000 Hz, respectively. The force signals are conditioned by strain gauge conditioners (2B31J, Analog Devices Inc.) which have a 3 pole Bessel filter having a cutoff frequency set at 200 Hz.
